<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12066f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12066f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12066f"> 66(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bishop Maine prevents / him cursing horsethieves</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Saint was passing on to Magh-Luirg <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> when his horses were stolen &hellip; The Saint was induced to refrain from pronouncing a malediction on the robbers by Bishop Maine who interposed and begged forgiveness on their behalf, for they were his kinsmen. <small> William Canon Fleming, <a name="WFSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WFSP"><cite title="source">The Life of St Patrick: Apostle of Ireland</cite></a> (1905) 113</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
